==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water mite
<hw>Wa"ter mite`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any of
numerous species of aquatic mites belonging to <gen>Hydrachna</gen> and
allied genera of the family <fam>Hydrachnidae</fam>, usually having the
legs fringed and adapted for swimming. They are often red or red and
black in color, and while young are parasites of fresh-water insects and
mussels. Called also <altname>water tick</altname>, and <altname>water
spider</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1633 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

